My very best pulled pork takes 36 hours to make. 24 hour brine followed by 12 hour oven slow roast. It's worth every second!
A fantastic freezer friendly meal! The caramelized onion makes all the difference in these Pulled Pork Carnitas Quesadillas. Plus, tips on how to make the perfect quesadilla!
This slow cooker Pulled Pork with BBQ sauce will be the most tender, moist, and flavourful you've ever had in your life! High returns for minimal effort!!

recipe_name: Pumpkin Cake with Cream Cheese Frosting
description: A moist pumpkin cake topped with cream cheese frosting. Fast and easy to make with fresh or can pumpkin. Make bars, bundt cake, loaf or even muffins!
The perfect pumpkin pie with a silky filling that's not too sweet, scpied enough but not so that it overwhelms and the secret to NO CRACKS!!
A classic, super easy pumpkin soup that's fast to make. Thick, creamy and dreamy, with sweet pumpkin flavour and great savoury undertones!
Purple rice is a garlicky, butter rice that owes its vibrant colour to red cabbage! Love this 2-in-1 side that combines starch + lots of veg.
This authentic Indian ground beef recipe is called "Qeema" and is an amazingly simple yet complex tasting curried Indian dish.
Crispy on the outside, juicy, seasoned and molten inside. The only Quesadilla recipe you'll ever need - choose from chicken, beef or vegetarian quesadillas!

A homemade Quiche Lorraine is one of those things reserved for special occasions that puts store bought to shame. Surprise yourself with how easy it is to make a homemade quiche crust - or make life easy using frozen pastry or a pre prepared pie crust.
These Quiche Toast Cups are mini quiches, made in a muffin tin using sandwich bread! Filled with bacon and cheesy goodness, these cute bites are irresistible.
This Baked Zucchini recipe is a really easy way to cook zucchini in the oven that's extremely tasty. 3 minutes prep. Love the crunchy parmesan bits!
Asian Beef Ramen Noodles made with caramelised ground beef, a tangle of noodles and a secret 4 ingredient Asian sauce, finished with sesame seeds!
The quickest and BEST way to make Cheesy Garlic Bread - drizzle with melted garlic butter, bake, top with cheese and melt. Outrageously good!
This Risoni recipe tastes like risotto.... except it's far quicker to make! Creamy parmesan no-cream sauce, chicken, plenty of veg - fab quick dinner idea.
Who says the pastry has to be baked ON the pie filling? FREE FORM it, and make chicken pot pie from scratch in just 20 minutes!
20 minute Chicken Tacos made with a homemade chicken taco seasoning that does double duty to flavour the shredded chicken AND make the taco sauce!
Midweek secret weapon - ultra tasty Satay Peanut Stir Fry sauce, great for chicken, beef, pork, prawns or tofu. Tastes like Chinese takeout satay!
Quick tomato chutney created especially to be used as a burger sauce, though I use it just like normal chutney. Love that it's less sweet!
My all time favourite Quinoa Salad. Garlic Ginger Asian Dressing, lots of colourful veggies, finished with crushed wasabi peas - best part!
Buttery oatmeal base, raspberry jam filling and crumbly topping, these Raspberry Jam Oat Bars are one of the fastest bars to make!
Ratatouille is a French Provencal vegetable stew that's bursting with summery Mediterranean flavours! Simple & humble, yet a stunner!

recipe_name: Real Chinese All Purpose Stir Fry Sauce (Charlie!)
description: Authentic, all purpose Chinese stir fry sauce that is truly restaurant quality. Made in a couple of minutes, store it in the fridge for weeks!
Vegetarian {vegan} Tofu Chow Mein, an authentic recipe on the table in 15 minutes. The caramelised tofu is especially delicious!
A little bit lemony, a little bit cheesy and a whole lot of yum, Broccoli Pasta is an emergency quick dinner idea or 2-in-1 veg carb side dish. 12 minute broccoli recipe!

recipe_name: Red Cabbage, Carrot and Mint Salad
description: A versatile red cabbage salad that goes with most cuisines, including Middle Eastern, Asian, Mexican, European, Italian and Southern.

recipe_name: Red Potato Salad with Bacon and Corn (no mayo!)
description: A striking Red Potato Salad rich with bacon and charred sweet corn. No mayonnaise potato salad - you won't miss mayo in this one!
This is the BEST Red Velvet Cake recipe, and with my tips, it is so easy to make. Bright red, perfect, velvety sponge with fluffy cream cheese frosting.
In this recipe my Red Velvet Cookies are made from scratch and taste just like red velvet cupcakes! The cookie is soft, moist and "cake like" and topped with cream cheese frosting.
rue to the name, these Red Velvet Cupcakes with cream cheese frosting have a "velvety" crumb with superior buttery flavour.
The Vietnamese fried rice version of Vietnamese red rice. Flavoured with tomato with golden bits of ham, egg and peas, great quick dinner!
Quick to make Restaurant Style Salsa. Great to serve with corn chips at gatherings or as a starter, or use as a sauce for tacos, burritos, nachos and quesadillas!
Piled high with warm, fall-apart homemade pastrami, sauerkraut, Russian dressing and Swiss cheese, this Reuben Sandwich recipe is epic!

recipe_name: Rice Pilaf with Nuts and Dried Fruit
description: A beautifully fragrant Rice Pilaf with pistachios, almonds and dried fruit. Perfect for your holiday feasting table or a side for a Middle Eastern meal!
Ricotta pancakes / hotcakes are extra moist and fluffy. Easy to make, go wild with the toppings! Based on Bill Granger's recipe.

recipe_name: Ricotta and Spinach Puff Pastry Bites
description: Made in a muffin tin, these Ricotta and Spinach Puff Pastry Bites are a cute twist on traditional cheese and spinach triangles. 1 sheet of pastry makes 9 of these! These would be perfect for a picnic, an afternoon tea or even the kids' lunchboxes. Check the recipe out for details!
The only Rissoles recipe you'll ever need. Plump, extra juicy and extra tasty, these can be made with beef, lamb, pork, chicken or turkey.

Roast Chicken slathered with a garlic-herb-lemon butter then oven roasted to golden crispy perfection. Juicy on the inside, and served with liquid gold pan juices loaded with flavour, this is THE Roast Chicken recipe you'll make over and over again!
The classic Aussie roast lamb leg with a killer gravy! Easy to make with a few simple tips. Cook times table and cooking video included!

recipe_name: Roast Pumpkin, Spinach and Feta Salad
description: Try this Roast Pumpkin, Spinach and Feta Salad for your next Sunday lunch! A magical combination of ingredients, very easy to make.

recipe_name: Roast Turkey Breast with Garlic Herb Butter
description: Garlic Herb Roast Turkey Breast with herb butter smeared under the skin which bastes the turkey as it roasts. Juicy inside, golden skin, this is epic!
Just a really quick, very tasty way to prepare roasted asparagus: cook in a hot oven with garlic, finish with lemon juice & parmesan. YUM!
Take the humble broccoli to a new level with the addition of parmesan & pangrittata (breadcrumbs). Prepare in 5 min, then just bake for 15 minutes!
Roasted broccolini with tahini sauce - an excellent, simple way to cook broccolini, brought to you courtesy of Yotam Ottelenghi.
The trick to making really great roasted cauliflower is to bake it in a hot oven. Do this, and you just need salt, pepper and a little oil!

recipe_name: Roasted Cauliflower with Almond Sauce (Ester Restaurant)
description: This roasted cauliflower is the signature dish from Ester Restaurant which is one of Sydney's trendiest restaurants. It's not like me to order a cauliflower at a restaurant but I'm so glad I did because it was sensational! So I was thrilled to find the chef's recipe. And it's SO easy to make!

recipe_name: Roasted Flat Mushrooms with Green Onion, Thyme & Butter

description: This Roasted Parmesan Crusted Cauliflower is quick, easy and off-the-charts delicious! Try it for dinner tonight - as a side, or as a meatless meal!

recipe_name: Roasted Pumpkin with Maple, Chili and Feta
description: Roasted pumpkin with maple syrup, walnuts, roasted pumpkin seeds, chilli and feta. My new favourite way with pumpkin!

recipe_name: Roasted Pumpkin with Yogurt Sauce and Pine Nuts
description: Here's an excellent way to quickly dress up roasted pumpkin - casually drizzle with a lemon yoghurt sauce. It's superb!

recipe_name: Roasted Sweet Potato Salad with Honey Lemon Dressing
description: This spectacular Roasted Sweet Potato Salad with Honey Lemon Dressing is made with arugula / rocket, pecans, bacon and goats cheese / feta. Perfect pairing of flavours and textures!
These Roasted Sweet Potato Stacks have crispy edges, are buttery, salty and sweet with a hint of rosemary. Terrific Sweet Potato side dish!
Rustic, simple and fabulous - traditional Italian Saltimbocca recipe. One of the fastest meals you can make from scratch!
Samosa recipe - just like you get from the very best Indian restaurants! Flaky pastry, moist spiced potato filling, NOT GREASY!

recipe_name: San Fran Chicken Salad with Yoghurt Ranch Dressing
description: Inspired by Souvla restaurant in San Francisco, this Chicken Salad with Yoghurt Ranch Dressing is one of the best chicken salads I've ever had!

Satay chicken noodle salad is everything you love about satay chicken.... in salad form! Colourful shredded vegetables, noodles and satay chicken drizzled with the most incredible satay peanut dressing.
A fast and easy satay chicken with a lip smacking peanut sauce! Brilliant for BBQ - or cook it on the stove OR broil them! The peanut sauce is utterly addictive - you'll wish you doubled the recipe!
Sauce Vierge is a French modern classic sauce that's like a salsa and vinaigrette. Excellent summery sauce for fish and all seafood!
All the breakfast essentials, in one golden cheesy bake! This Breakfast Casseroles tastes just like a country breakfast fry up - hence the name. Perfect for feeding a crowd AND it can be made ahead.

recipe_name: Sausage Bake with Potatoes and Gravy
description: A Sausage Bake with Potatoes, Carrots and Onions, all smothered in Gravy made in ONE PAN! Sort of like a casserole, with golden brown sausages and the most incredible gravy.
Sausage Pasta with up sausage that are like mini sausage meatballs, tossed in a super tomato pasta sauce. Quick, easy, really delicious dinner!
Incredible homemade Sausage Rolls like what you get from the best patisseries!! The secret is sautéed onion, garlic, celery & BACON.

These Sausage and Egg Breakfast Potato Skins are a new way to serve up your old breakfast staples. As the name suggests, this is a potato stuffed with sausage and topped with an egg and cheese! A great recipe that can be prepared ahead and cooked at leisure.
Sautéed Green Beans with garlic is a wonderful, classic preparation for a green beans recipe. Totally delicious, quick and easy.

recipe_name: Sautéed Brussels Sprouts in Carbonara Sauce

description: Savoury Cheese muffins: Cheesy, buttery, garlicky and so moist, these taste like cheesy garlic bread! This is the stuff savoury muffin dreams are made of. Dangerously quickly and easy to make.
There is nothing quite like a freshly made schnitzel. Extra crunchy and golden, make this with pork, chicken, veal or turkey! Plus a mushroom gravy recipe!

Really easy, classic plain scones you'll make again and again. 3 ingredients, and in the oven in under 10 minutes! Soft and fluffy inside, serve with copious amounts of jam and cream for the ultimate classic afternoon experience.
No one should tell you how to take your eggs. But everyone should know how to make scrambled eggs well! 60 seconds, soft, creamy, custardy. Perfection!
This Seafood Gratin is made with your choice of seafood and pasta baked in a creamy béchamel sauce (no cream) with a crunchy breadcrumb and cheese topping!
An easy seafood pasta recipe - classic Spaghetti Marinara. Pasta tossed in a luscious tomato sauce with mixed seafood - incredibly fast & easy to make!
Self Saucing Butterscotch Pudding magic - one batter transforms into a warm, fudgey pudding cake AND a butterscotch sauce! Quick and super easy dessert!
Just roll the salmon in sesame seeds, drizzle with oil and bake. You'll be amazed how well it sticks and love how crispy this Sesame Crusted Salmon is!
Here's a tofu recipe you'll actually WANT to make - Sesame Crusted Tofu Steaks! Crispy sesame crust with Teriyaki Sauce. Quick and easy!
Sesame Noodles tossed in a fabulous Asian Sesame Peanut Dressing! Terrific served at room temperature or warm, this is a great Asian side dish.
Secret to a great lentil salad - cook lentils in a simple flavoured broth or marinate can lentils. Sprinkle with feta, drizzle with lemon salad dressing!
I say this is the best baked eggs in the world, but actually, they can be poached instead of baked!! Just one rule - crusty bread is a must.

Shepherd's Pie is one of those foods that brings a smile to everyone’s face – especially when you get seconds! A deeply savoury lamb and vegetable filling topped with creamy mashed potato and a golden cheese crust, it's straightforward to make and is brilliant for making ahead.
Shepherd's Pie potato skins! A neat way to use up the potato you scoop out. That moment when you cut through the golden crust, the creamy mash then that filling comes oozing out....

recipe_name: Shirred Eggs (Baked Eggs with Spinach & Mushrooms)
description: Shirred Eggs - baked eggs on a bed of garlic butter mushrooms and spinach, topped with bubbly cream and parmesan! Quick, easy, so delicious!

recipe_name: Shortbread Cookie Sandwich With Dulce De Leche
description: These Shortbread Cookie Sandwiches are just 3 ingredients and take only 10 min to prepare! Filled with Dulce De Leche for a sweet Latino twist, these easy little sweets require just 1 ingredient and 15 sec to prepare!
I’m a firm believer that shortbread cookies should be sinfully buttery and delectably tender. Make these iconic biscuits with just flour, butter and sugar!
Discover the restaurant secret of making a sauce using prawn shells - amazing flavour, quick and easy! This prawn pasta recipe will stand out from others you've tried thanks to this technique.
Sicilian chicken spaghetti - tender shredded chicken tossed in a tomato garlic pasta sauce with olives and any other antipasto-type things you have!
The most iconic, best crab recipe in the world - Singapore Chilli Crab! Traditionally made with mud crab but can be made with any crabs.

With its signature hint of curry flavour and yellow hue, Singapore Noodles are made with thin rice noodles, prawns, Chinese Pork, egg and red capsicum. Don’t fret if you don’t have all the ingredients – this is worth making with whatever you have!

recipe_name: Sirloin Steak with Pesto, Capsicum & Flatbread
description: Steak with Pesto and chargrilled capsicum and homemade flatbread. A quick dinner that's full of flavour and entirely homemade from scratch, including the flatbread.
Siu Mai is the first thing you grab off the trolleys when you descend upon your favourite Yum Cha. And now you can get your Shumai fix on demand!
A classic Chimichurri Steak recipe! Made with parsley, oregano, garlic, olive oil and vinegar - so fast to make in a food processor, and tastes incredible!
Skip the packet mixes and can sauces. Homemade Sloppy Joes are SO EASY and tastes better! This Sloppy Joe recipe is a keeper you'll make again and again.

recipe_name: Slow Cooked Beef Cheeks in Red Wine Sauce
description: These slow cooked beef cheeks are braised in red wine. So meltingly tender you can eat it with a spoon with a luscious smooth sauce with incredible flavour.

recipe_name: Slow Cooked Lamb Shanks in Red Wine Sauce
description: These slow cooked lamb shanks are meltingly tender and are braised in a rich red wine sauce. Super easy to make in the slow cooker OR on the stove!
This meltingly tender Slow Cooked Lamb Shawarma is the stuff food dreams are made of!! Slathered in a Shawarma Spice Rub then slow cooked to fall apart perfection, try finishing this on the BBQ!
This slow cooked lamb shoulder infused with rosemary and garlic is so tender you don't need a carving knife. Super easy, tastier & cheaper than lamb leg!

recipe_name: Slow Cooker BBQ Pulled Pork Sandwich
description: This Slow Cooker BBQ Pulled Pork Sandwich is made with tender pork smothered in BBQ Sauce and topped with Coleslaw. Finger lickin' good!

recipe_name: Slow Cooker Beef Brisket with BBQ Sauce
description: Ultra tender, juicy Slow Cooker Beef Brisket smothered in a homemade BBQ Sauce. Slow cooker, pressure cooker or stove - then caramelise on the BBQ or oven!
Slow Cooker Beef Stroganoff - fall apart slow cooked beef in a luscious, creamy Stroganoff sauce with buttery garlic mushrooms! This is a magnificant stew.
Real Chinese Beef & Broccoli, but made in a slow cooker! Super convenient, this Slow Cooker Beef and Broccoli transforms budget cuts of beef and you can make it freezer friendly!

recipe_name: Slow Cooker Crispy Chinese Shredded Chicken
description: Chinese Shredded Chicken - Slow cooked in a classic Chinese braising liquid, shredded then pan fried until golden. 5 minutes to prepare, freezes perfectly, great for fast midweek meals.

recipe_name: Slow Cooker Honey Buffalo Chicken Sliders
description: Chicken sliders made in the SLOW COOKER cooked in an awesome sweet and mildly spicy Buffalo sauce! Plus directions to make this on the stove or even in a pressure cooker, AND an optional blue cheese sauce. These Honey Buffalo Chicken Sliders are a great way to feed a crowd with minimal effort!
Slow Cooker Marinara Sauce takes just 5 minutes of prep and is made in a slow cooker. The result is incredible depth of flavour which store bought pasta sauce simply doesn't compare to.
Slow Cooker Mexican Chicken Soup tastes like chicken enchiladas! Sensational slow cooker soup that's quick to prep, loaded with flavour. Healthy & hearty!
A Slow Cooker Pork Loin roast that's cooked long and slow in an amazing honey butter garlic sauce until fork tender yet sliceable!

5 minutes to put the chicken in the slow cooker in the morning then with 15 minutes effort you'll have an insanely juicy golden roast chicken for dinner. This Slow Cooker Roast Chicken is an absolute crowd pleaser!
This Slow Cooker Roast Lamb Leg is the easiest, most succulent lamb leg you'll ever have, with an incredible gravy. Minutes of prep, then set and forget!
Slow Cooker Shredded Beef Chili is your favourite Chilli Con Carne made with juicy pulled beef that soaks up the rich sauce! Quick prep, set and forget.
This Slow Roast Leg of Lamb is going to take your next Sunday roast to a whole new level! Ultra tender meat, this is incredibly easy and very forgiving.
Classic Italian beef ragu with shredded beef. Easy to prepare, cooked long and slow to get an incredible depth of flavour for a rich luscious sauce.
This is a recipe for Pork Belly that's slow roasted to make the flesh ultra tender & juicy, with impossibly perfect, crazy crispy crackling!
Smashed Cucumber Salad is a "thing" in Asia! Cucumbers bashed so they burst open so the dressing drips into all the cracks and crevices. Serve with all things Asian!
Homemade Smoked Salmon Dip has an incredible real smoked salmon flavour that you simply can't buy in tubs from the supermarket! Made with cream cheese, lemon, dill and smoked salmon.
Smoked Salmon Potato Rosti Stack is a stack of potato rosti / hash browns topped with smoked salmon and a dollop of sour cream or creme fraiche. Great for a lazy brunch!

recipe_name: Smoked Salmon and Egg Breakfast Mille-feuille
description: Puff pastry with soft scrambled eggs and smoked salmon layers: Smoked Salmon and Egg Breakfast Mille-feuille is my interpretation of a breakfast Mille-feuille! Just 5 minutes prep for this recipe, and a very elegant breakfast / brunch idea.
Sausage and Rice Casserole punches way above its weight for effort vs results! Use any smoked sausages - kransky, kielbasa (Polish sausages), chorizo.

recipe_name: Smoked Trout Dip or Spread (Budget Gourmet)
description: This Smoked Trout Dip / Potted Smoked Trout is an elegant starter that is easy to make and easy on the wallet. Whole smoked trout is one of the cheapest items at the seafood shop!
The only flatbread recipe you'll ever need! Soft and pliable, perfect for using as a wrap. No yeast, and hardly any kneading. Quick to make on stove or BBQ!
No knead, no special equipment required for these beautiful golden, soft and fluffy dinner rolls. Just combine the ingredients in a bowl and mix with a wooden spoon!

recipe_name: Southern Thai Tumeric Chicken (Grilled or Baked)
description: This Southern Thai Chicken is sweet, sticky, and savoury. Simple to make, terrific for grilling or baking. Authentic Thai at home!
A thick, rich Bolognese with great depth of flavour. Made in just 30 minutes, this is a Spaghetti Bolognese you'll make over and over again...
Spaghetti alla Puttanesca is a traditional Italian pasta sauce made with tomato, olives, capers, anchovies and garlic. Fast, easy, delicious!
The one thing that sets this Spanakopita apart from the rest? Using raw rather than cooked spinach for the filling. Better flavour & texture!
An authentic, EPIC Spanish Paella! Easy to make with step by step photos, load it up with seafood, just use chicken or even make it vegetarian!
Spanish Romesco Sauce, made from chargrilled capsicums, is a magic sauce that is incredibly versatile! Use it as a dip, spread, sauce, marinade, and stir into soups and stews!

A hearty Sicilian Italian Chicken Casserole. Crispy chicken in a delicious tomato sauce with olives and capsicums, on the table in 30 minutes.

recipe_name: Spicy Joint's Creamy Sesame Sauce Lettuce Salad
description: Creamy Sesame Sauce Lettuce Salad - copycat from an authentic Sichuan restaurant called "Spicy Joint" in Sydney that I'm completely mad for!
This authentic marinade and sauce for this Spicy Korean Pork Stir Fry is ridiculously easy and INSANELY delicious! BIG BOLD Korean flavours!

recipe_name: Spicy Little Muffin Tin Chicken Tostadas
description: Great little party appetiser, Spicy Little Muffin Tin Chicken Tostadas are fast to prepare and can be made ahead! Cut the rounds using an empty can and bake in a muffin tin!
My Spicy Parmesan Party Popcorn is the fastest, cheapest, easiest party food recipe in my repertoire. Minutes to prepare and costs less than $2 for an enormous bowl!
Spinach Artichoke Dip is always a hit! This is beautifully soft and creamy, so crackers and chips won't break when scooped. Super quick and easy.
Beef Cannelloni stuffed with a juicy spinach and beef filling, topped with plenty of sauce and melty cheese. Cosy food that's mouthwateringly delicious!
Tastes like spinach and ricotta stuffed shells - but without the labor! Creamy and cheesy, fast to prepare and made from scratch. Great midweek meal!
Imagine coming home to this Spinach Ricotta Cannelloni.... a perfectly seasoned juicy filling with a simple, tasty tomato sauce. Great for freezing!
These Spinach and Ricotta Rolls are fantastic for parties and snacking! Great for making ahead and freezing, the filling is moist, cheesy and juicy.

recipe_name: Spinach and Ricotta Rotolo (Italian Lasagna Roll Ups)
description: Baked spinach and ricotta rotolo: It's like cannelloni, but with crunchy browned bits! Everyday ingredients, a familiar dish, turned into something memorable.
Stuffed shells - don't mess around with hot floppy pre cooked shells! Just stuff them raw and bake in loads of sauce. Works 100% perfectly!
You've never really had a spring roll until you've tried a homemade one. With the quick video tutorial, you'll be a Spring Roll recipe master in no time!
Spring Salad - just a really great, elegant salad using spring vegetables: asparagus, snow peas, peas with baby cos lettuce and goats cheese.
Standing Rib Roast is the ULTIMATE Roast Beef! Also known as Prime Rib, it's the tastiest, juiciest and most tender cut of beef.
How to cook steak like a chef - baste with garlic thyme butter as it cooks! It makes the nost of great quality steaks and fancies up economical steak!
Sink your teeth into this juicy steak sandwich loaded with tender beef, caramelised onion, garlic aioli, mustard, rocket and tomato. Spectacular!
Sticky Baked Chicken Thighs is what you make when you need a quick and easy recipe for boneless skinless chicken thighs. Love the sweet savoury glaze!
My family recipe for the perfect Sticky Chinese Chicken Wings, tweaked and perfected over years with many heated debates! Terrific chicken wing marinade.

recipe_name: Sticky Chicken Drumsticks in Chinese Plum Sauce
description: Oven baked sticky chicken drumsticks slathered in the most incredible yet ridiculously simple Chinese Plum Sauce glaze. Total crowd pleaser!

recipe_name: Sticky Chicken With Vegetable Fried Rice
description: Sticky Chicken With Vegetable Fried Rice is a great and FAST midweek meal that you can prepare ahead! Think of it as a Chinese takeaway meal in a bowl.
Sticky Toffee Pudding - you're my favourite and always will be. I love how easy you are to make, and how there's plenty of butterscotch sauce! Also known as Sticky Date Pudding.
A holiday spiced marinade makes this glazed Christmas Chicken extra moist and flavourful as well as making it ultra sticky!
This sticky grilled chicken is THE chicken marinade I reach for when I want a guaranteed winner. The smell when this hits the BBQ is outrageous!
No marinating required, this Baked Honey Soy Chicken is made with just a pantry essentials. The glaze is sticky, sweet and utterly irresistible!
I call this a Sticky Pantry Chicken Thighs recipe because it's a recipe you can make using pantry staples! Tastes like a sweet, savoury country sauce.
Still the best Stuffing I've had in my life! A pork sausage stuffing recipe made with bread, apple, pecans, sage and thyme. 100% incredible!
Stir Fried Noodles with Peanut Sauce - tastes like satay peanut stir fries you get at Chinese restaurants in Australia. So easy and SO GOOD!
An epic classic Stovetop Macaroni and Cheese that just happens to be made in one pot! 30 minutes, silky sauce, very easy, + 1 min video tutorial.
Bursting with fresh strawberries, these Fresh Strawberry Bars have a buttery oat biscuit base and are finished off with a crumbly topping. Quick & easy!
To say this Upside Down Strawberry Cake is bursting with fresh strawberry flavour is an understatement! Easy, looks fabulous, tastes amazing.
A fabulous strawberry dessert recipe that's easy to prepare! This Strawberry Crumble with the signature crumbly topping covering strawberries in syrup. The smell is outrageously good!
A creamy, no churn Strawberry Ice Cream with real strawberry flavour that money can't buy! Creamy, scoopable, no ice crystals at all, no ice cream maker required!

recipe_name: Strawberry Nutella French Toast Roll Ups
description: Fast and easy to make, these Strawberry Nutella French Toast Roll Ups taste like a doughnut! And just 254 calories per serving!
Strawberry Salad - pretty as a picture and tastes even better! A bit of a show off salad made with spinach, candied pecans, avocado, feta and a poppyseed dressing.

recipe_name: Strawberry Spinach Salad with Strawberry Balsamic Dressing
description: A stunning Chef recipe for a Strawberry Spinach Salad. Strawberries, spinach, candied pecans, blue cheese and an incredible Strawberry Balsamic Dressing.

recipe_name: Sun Dried Tomato, Spinach & Cheese Baked Stuffed Chicken Breast
description: Juicy chicken breast slathered in Italian flavours then stuffed with spinach, sun dried tomato and cheese. 5 minutes prep, no marinating required!

recipe_name: Super Easy French Onion Soup Dip
description: This French Onion Dip is made with soup mix - it's soft, cheaper and so much tastier than store bought dip. 80's throwback that will be here forever!

recipe_name: Super Low Cal Healthy Creamy Vegetable Soup
description: This Creamy Healthy Vegetable Soup is super low cal, gluten free and incredibly delicious. The secret - a seasoned broth made with zucchini, cauliflower, onion and garlic. Imagine the possibilities!
Supreme Soy Noodles are my go-to Asian noodles to serve alongside Asian mains yet tasty enough to devour plain. Quick and super easy.
Extra soft, extra juicy, extra tasty Swedish Meatballs with two little tips that make all the difference. Smothered in an epic gravy for Swedish Meatballs!
A good amount of leek and onion plus hefty tablespoon of cumin makes this sweet potato soup anything but boring!

Just 5 minutes preparation to make this Shredded Sweet Soy Sauce Chicken Breast recipe on the stove, slow cooker or pressure cooker! Serve on rice, noodles, in lettuce cups, inside rice paper wraps or anything else you fancy.

recipe_name: Sweet Tart Crust (French  pastry – Pâte Sucrée)
description: Classic Sweet Tart Crust, called Pâte Sucrée in French, this pastry is superior to shortcrust - better flavour and easier to work with.

recipe_name: Sweet and Sour Chicken Stir Fry
description: This Sweet and Sour Chicken Stir Fry is made with a sauce that truly tastes like what you get at good Chinese restaurants. Incredibly fast and easy!

recipe_name: Sweet and Sour Pork - best ever!
description: The best ever Sweet and Sour Pork recipe is loaded with tricks the Chinese have been using for centuries: double dredge, double fry, tenderised pork!
Swiss Mushroom Burgers - a big, juicy vegetarian burger stuffed with a garlic butter roasted mushroom (portobello, BBQ flat) topped with swiss cheese. YUM.
This is a simple but exotic dish of Syrian Chicken that is incredibly aromatic. It is made with everyday ingredients and takes just on 15 minutes to prepare to pop in the oven.
A simple taco sauce that's quick to make and rivals store bought! Serve with tacos, or as a dipping sauce for burritos, quesadillas or corn chips.
Everything you know and love about tacos - in soup form! This is an easy Taco Soup that is thick, hearty, warm and an absolute crowd pleaser.

recipe_name: Taco Stack with Pork Carnitas or Chicken
description: Taco stacks - fun and fabulous to eat, fast and easy to make! Layers of tortillas, Pork Carnitas or Chicken, salsa, melted cheese and plenty of toppings!
An authentic recipe for Teriyaki Chicken using homemade Teriyaki Sauce, taught to me by my Japanese mother. Very easy, only 4 ingredients.

Noodles and salmon tossed with Teriyaki Sauce makes for a tasty quick and easy dinner that's an all-in-one complete meal.
Thai Basil Chicken is a gold standard Thai chicken recipe that's incredibly fast and easy to make, and truly tastes as good as Thai restaurants!

Not just another Thai Beef Salad recipe ....This is made with one little change to create a dressing from an award winning Thai restaurant, arguably one of the best in the world outside of Thailand. (PS No trip to the Asian store required!)
